JOHANNESBURG - This week the Extreme Fighting Championship (EFC) announced that former lightweight champion Dave ‘Pain Train’ Mazany (16-7) will be facing incumbent Martin ‘The Punisher’ van Staden (19-9) for the golden buckle on the 11th of August in Cape Town, setting up the biggest fight yet in the promotion’s 2018 calendar. The Clinch caught up with the popular Alaskan in Liverpool, England where he was cornering his sister, UFC bantamweight, Gina ‘Danger’ Mazany (5-2,) to ask him about the fight and his desire for a rerun with MVS’s teammate, Don ‘Magic Man’ Madge (7-3-1) eNCA